      "name": "Model-form adequacy — literature review synthesis",
      "description": "A structured survey of 14 published studies on power-law hemolysis models was conducted. The review concluded that the Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation used in the CFD model is consistent with the majority of published experimental datasets for centrifugal pumps. This result is presented as the primary evidence that the model form is adequate for absolute hemolysis prediction.",
